Analyze Intrusion Case Study: Human-Operated Ransomware
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Identify common attack vectors used in human-operated ransomware campaigns
Map attack techniques to the MITRE ATT&CK framework
Perform forensic analysis of ransomware attack artifacts
Understand the progression of a sophisticated ransomware attack
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Linux command line
Familiarity with network protocols and log analysis
Knowledge of cybersecurity fundamentals
Understanding of file systems and process analysis
